text: Bradley Vincent (born 30 November 1991) is a Mauritian competitive swimmer. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the men's 100 metre freestyle. He starts at the Swimming World Cup 2017 and broke his own record (22,82) about 50m Freestyle. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Mauritian male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Mauritius Category:Swimmers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Mauritius Category:Swimmers at the 2014 Commonwealth Games Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Commonwealth Games Category:Male freestyle swimmers
